          <details class="bg-surface-700 border border-surface-600 rounded-xl group">
            <summary class="flex items-center p-5 font-semibold text-lg cursor-pointer hover:text-accent transition-colors">Can ShipLint check apps built with Cursor, Copilot, or Claude?</summary>
            <div class="px-5 pb-5 pl-12 text-muted leading-relaxed">
              <p><strong class="text-white">Yes â€” in fact, that's exactly what ShipLint is designed for.</strong></p>
              <p class="mt-3">AI coding tools like Cursor, GitHub Copilot, and Claude are excellent at generating functional Swift code. But they often miss Apple's <em>platform configuration</em> requirements â€” privacy manifests, entitlement declarations, usage description strings â€” because these aren't about code correctness, they're about App Store compliance.</p>
